      "reading_order": 1,
      "subsections": [
        {
          "title": "I. PROGRAM OBJECTIVES",
          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "To provide resources to States and eligible Indian Tribes to make available vouchers for post-secondary training and education, to youth who are likely to age out of foster care or who have been adopted or left for kinship guardianship from the public foster care system after age 16, or who were in foster care on or after their 17th birthday.",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false,
                  "lang": null
                }
              ],
              "lang": null,
              "reading_order": null
            }
          ],
          "reading_order": 2,
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "title": "II. PROGRAM PROCEDURES",
          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "The State completes the annual CFS-101 that provides an estimate of annual funds. The Administration of Children and Families (ACF) awards funds to states depending upon funding availability. These funds require a twenty-percent match which may consist of State funds or allowable in-kind match.",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false,
                  "lang": null
                }
              ],
              "lang": null,
              "reading_order": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Subrecipients submit an annual contract proposal to the State and funds are awarded. Subrecipients acquire their grant award via the N. C. DHHS Office of Procurement and Contracting procedures referenced at\n",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false,
                  "lang": null
                },
                {
                  "href": "http://www.pandc.nc.gov/documents/Procurement_Manual_5_8_2013_interactive.pdf",
                  "text": "http://www.pandc.nc.gov/documents/Procurement_Manual_5_8_2013_interactive.pdf",
                  "title": null,
                  "opens_new_window": true
                },
                {
                  "text": ".\nFunds are distributed to the subrecipient on a monthly basis upon submission of a DSS-1571 invoice to the State.",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false,
                  "lang": null
                }
              ],
              "lang": null,
              "reading_order": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Eligible youth are required to apply for funding by completing the subrecipient application on line. Eligibility is determined by the NC State LINKS Program and communicated to the subrecipient. Funds are distributed to eligible applicants depending upon need and funding availability up to $5,000 per year and upon verification of their enrollment in a post-secondary or vocational institution. Funds may be used for cost of attendance and other allowable expenses.",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false,
                  "lang": null
                }
              ],
              "lang": null,
              "reading_order": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Subrecipients are monitored by the NC State LINKS Program in accordance to the NC Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Social Services Subrecipient Monitoring Plan – Contracts, found at: NC Sub-Recipient Monitoring Plan.",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false,
                  "lang": null
                }
              ],
              "lang": null,
              "reading_order": null
            }
          ],
          "reading_order": 3,
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "title": "III. COMPLIANCE REQUIREMENTS",
          "elements": [
            {
              "type": "blockquote",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "The Type of Compliance Requirements can be found in Section B in the link: 2020 Agency Matrix for Federal Programs. This matrix incorporates the OMB Compliance Supplement “Part 2 - Matrix of Compliance Requirement.” A State Agency may have added a compliance requirement that the OMB matrix in Part 2 has a “N” (Not Applicable).",
                  "bold": false,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false,
                  "lang": null
                }
              ],
              "citation": null,
              "lang": null,
              "reading_order": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Crosscutting Requirements: The compliance requirements in the Division of Social Services “Crosscutting Requirements” in Section D (Supplement #DSS-0) are applicable to this grant.",
                  "bold": true,
                  "italic": false,
                  "underline": false,
                  "strikethrough": false,
                  "superscript": false,
                  "subscript": false,
                  "code": false,
                  "lang": null
                }
              ],
              "lang": null,
              "reading_order": null
            }
          ],
          "reading_order": 4,
          "subsections": [
            {
              "title": "A. ACTIVITIES ALLOWED OR UNALLOWED",
              "elements": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Funds may be used to provide vouchers for post-secondary education and training to youth who are/were in foster at age 17 otherwise eligible for services under the State’s or Tribe’s Chafee Foster Care Independence Program. Vouchers may also be provided to youth who leave foster care for adoption or kinship guardianship after age 16, or who are still in foster care on or after their 17th birthday. Vouchers can be provided to youth up to the age of 23, as long as they are participating in the program at age 21 and are making satisfactory progress toward completing their course of study or training. Vouchers provided to individuals may be available for the cost of attending an institution of higher education (as defined in section 472 of the Higher Education Act) and shall not exceed the lesser of $5,000 per grant year or the total cost of attendance as defined in section 472 of the Higher Education Act.",
                      "bold": false,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "No more than ten percent (10%) of the federal grant is dedicated to the administration of these funds. That portion of the funds is distributed between salaries and other administrative costs. The remainder of the funds may only be used for cash vouchers for the eligible students to pay for allowable expenses that are included in their cost of attendance. Vouchers are directly paid to third party vendors.",
                      "bold": false,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Recommended Audit Procedures:",
                      "bold": true,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Determine that students receiving Educational Training Vouchers are eligible for these funds by meeting all the criteria in section C, below;",
                      "bold": false,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Documentation of vouchers from Foster Care to Success specifies that the student is eligible for ETV and that any expenditure is allowable under the principles of the Act.",
                      "bold": false,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Documentation of administrative expenditures from Foster Care to Success is allowable under the budget.",
                      "bold": false,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                }
              ],
              "reading_order": 5,
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "title": "B. ALLOWABLE COSTS/COST PRINCIPLES",
              "elements": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Funds provided to the subrecipient for administration may only be used for salaries, annual audit expenses, web-based application, case management services, mentoring services, marketing and promotional materials, insurance, equipment, and supplies.",
                      "bold": false,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Funds provided to or on behalf of applicants may be used for:",
                      "bold": false,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                },
                {
                  "type": "list",
                  "list_type": "unordered",
                  "items": [
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Tuition and fees;",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    },
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "On-campus room and board or a housing and food allowance for off-campus students;",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    },
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Allowances for books, supplies, transportation, loan fees, and, if applicable dependent care;",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    },
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Costs related to a disability;",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    },
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Miscellaneous expenses, including rental or purchase of a personal computer;",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    },
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Reasonable costs associated with eligible study-abroad programs.",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "reading_order": null
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "All grantees that expend State funds (including federal funds passed through the N. C. Department of Health and Human Services) are required to comply with the cost principles described in the N. C. Administrative Code at 09 NCAC 03M .0201.",
                      "bold": false,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                }
              ],
              "reading_order": 6,
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "title": "E. ELIGIBILITY",
              "elements": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Applicants are eligible for up to $5,000 in financial assistance to attend a qualifying educational or vocational training institution which provides post-secondary coursework. The award is based on the total cost of attendance less other federal grants and scholarships. The award may not exceed $5,000.",
                      "bold": false,
                      "italic": false,
                      "underline": false,
                      "strikethrough": false,
                      "superscript": false,
                      "subscript": false,
                      "code": false,
                      "lang": null
                    }
                  ],
                  "lang": null,
                  "reading_order": null
                },
                {
                  "type": "list",
                  "list_type": "unordered",
                  "items": [
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Applicant is now between 18 and 20 years of age. If now 21 to 23 years of age, must have received ETV funds prior to 21st birthday and;",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    },
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Applicant was in foster care on or after his/her 17th birthday or was adopted from foster care on or after his/her 16th birthday or placed in a relative guardianship on or after his/her 16th birthday and;",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    },
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Applicant is attending a qualifying institution of post-secondary learning. Full time students qualify for up to $5,000 a year for all the above expenses; students attending part time qualify for up to $2,500 per year in tuition/fees, books, supplies, transportation and dependent-care expenses and;",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    },
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Applicant is either a U. S. Citizen or is a qualified resident alien.",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
                          "lang": null
                        }
                      ],
                      "nested_list": null,
                      "term": null,
                      "definition": null
                    },
                    {
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "text": "Applicant does not have more than $10,000 in personal reserves.",
                          "bold": false,
                          "italic": false,
                          "underline": false,
                          "strikethrough": false,
                          "superscript": false,
                          "subscript": false,
                          "code": false,
